messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/users/{id}

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Per-method acceptability (based only on the code, not on runtime/Express defaults):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the user routes at app.use('/api/users', userRoutes), so the base prefix is /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the route for the parameterized path is router.route('/:id') with the following explicit method handlers:
  - .delete(protect, admin, deleteUser)
  - .get(protect, admin, getUserById)
  - .put(protect, admin, updateUser)
  These map to the full path /api/users/:id, which is represented here as /api/users/{id}.
- No router.all(...) or similar catchâ€‘all is used, so "all methods" is false.
- Only methods explicitly registered in the code are considered acceptable per your instruction to base decisions on the code (not on framework behavior). Therefore GET, PUT and DELETE are true; HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE and PATCH are false.
